The city of dreams!!🏙️ A love letter to New York💌
I know it sounds so cliche, but the energy is different here. Everyone is here with a purpose and a passion to achieve a dream. I’ve met so many amazing entrepreneurs, models, actors, & creators, who moved to New York to achieve just that. This city continues to be a motivator and I’ve been able to attain so many goals I set for myself, simply by being in this environment. 

However, just as much as this city uplifts you, it also breaks you down 10x harder. There have been many months where I’ve felt defeated from this city. A city with so many opportunities, but many inconveniences. At the bare minimum day to day life, New York isn’t glamorous.

When you have a strong passion and a goal to achieve, you can overlook that and only focus on what the city has to offer. The people, the food, the energy, the cultures. New York has it all. Sometimes I also need to step back and remind myself why I moved here, so here is my love letter to this city🫶🏻

I still can’t believe this is my life !!🥹 A little recap from my holiday market I hosted on Saturday! Truly a “pinch me” moment as this is THE proudest moment of my career😭

I hosted this holiday market with nothing but hope and prayers that my big idea would work out! The only goal I had was for these 32 small businesses to feel supported and loved this holiday season!🎄

Once I saw the line of guests waiting to enter, I felt the biggest sigh of relief, and told myself “look kas you did it!!” All the late nights and months of nonstop planning paid off as the 32 vendors ended the night with a smile on their faces!☺️

Thank you to everyone who came out and supported this event!! I love y’all 🫶🏻🫶🏻🫶🏻

I curated one of the biggest small business holiday pop-ups in nyc🥹

32 amazing small businesses, 650 guests, and 1 gal from Hawai’i striving to make an impact in New York❤️

From touring venues, negotiating terms, coordinating the vendors, furniture, & photographer, marketing, taking introduction calls, writing up contracts, invoices, and so much more… THIS day made it all worth it🫶🏻

My career has always been focused on working with small businesses. I grew up being surrounded by family-owned and local businesses, which is something I became more appreciative of as I moved away from Hawai’i.

When I moved to New York, I had a difficult time finding my community and people I related to. I get homesick a lot, which is why I fly home for a couple of weeks every few months!😅

I decided that I wanted to create my own sense of family here in New York, which is why I put my heart and soul into @socialluxeclub 🤍

Creating a sense of community for entrepreneurs to find others to relate to, while also bringing people together to support them is something I am so proud of!

This is only the beginning and there is so much more to come!! Thank you x million for supporting the Social Luxe Club!🥰
